To write code for a Discord bot using Discord.js v14, follow these steps:

Step 1: Install Discord.js and required packages
```
npm install discord.js
npm install @discordjs/rest
npm install @discordjs/builders
```

Step 2: Create a new Node.js project and initialize it with the package.json file.
```
mkdir discord-bot
cd discord-bot
npm init -y
```

Step 3: Create a file named `index.js` and add the following code to it:
```js
const { Client, Intents, GatewayIntentBits } = require("discord.js");
const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });

client.once("ready", () => {
  console.log("Bot is ready!");
});

client.login("YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN");
```

Replace "YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN" with your actual Discord bot token.

Step 4: Create a folder named "commands" and create a new file named `ban.js` in the "commands" folder. Add the following code to `ban.js`:
```js
module.exports = {
  name: "ban",
  description: "Bans a user from the server",
  execute(message, args) {
    // Check if the user has permission to ban
    if (!message.member.permissions.has("BAN_MEMBERS")) {
      return message.reply("You don't have permission to ban members!");
    }

    // Check if a member was mentioned
    if (!args[0]) {
      return message.reply("You need to mention a user to ban!");
    }

    const member = message.mentions.members.first();

    // Check if the user is a member of the server
    if (!member) {
      return message.reply("Could not find that user!");
    }

    // Check if the user can be banned
    if (member.permissions.has("ADMINISTRATOR")) {
      return message.reply("Cannot ban an administrator!");
    }

    // Ban the user
    member.ban();
    message.reply(`${member.user.tag} has been banned`);
  },
};
```

Step 5: In `index.js`, import the command and add it to the client's collection of commands.
```js
const { Client, Intents, GatewayIntentBits } = require("discord.js");
const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });
const { ban } = require("./commands/ban");

client.once("ready", () => {
  console.log("Bot is ready!");
});

// Register command in client's collection of commands
client.commands = new Map();
client.commands.set(ban.name, ban);

client.login("YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN");
```

Step 6: To use this command, you need to set up an event handler for the "interactionCreate" event. The event handler will check if the interaction is a command interaction and then execute the corresponding command.

In `index.js`, add the following code:
```js
client.on("interactionCreate", async (interaction) => {
  if (!interaction.isCommand()) return;

  const command = client.commands.get(interaction.commandName);
  if (!command) return;

  try {
    await command.execute(interaction);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
    await interaction.reply({ content: "There was an error while executing this command!", ephemeral: true });
  }
});
```

Step 7: Save and run the code by using `node index.js`. Your Discord bot should now be up and running.

To use the "ban" command, you can simply type `/ban <user mention>` in any channel where your bot has permissions to ban members.

